wikipedia_page.main: Enda McNulty (born 1977 in Mullaghbawn, County Armagh, Northern Ireland) is an All Star winning Gaelic footballer for Armagh. He played football with his local club Mullaghbawn Cúchullain's in Armagh and was a member of the Armagh senior football team from 1996 to 2010. He earned his first and only All-Ireland medal in 2002, the same year in which he won his All Star award. He is also a sports psychologist.
